space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We iterate through the string twice: once to count the number of consecutive characters and another time to update the count of consecutive characters. The outer loop iterates from the beginning to the end of the string, and the inner loop iterates from the current index of the outer loop to the end of the string. The time complexity is O(n^2) because of the nested loops, where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(n) because we use an integer variable to store the count of consecutive characters. The energy implications are low because the solution only requires a few arithmetic operations and does not involve any complex algorithms or data structures.

